  <h3> If you are aged 44 to 69 you can now register for your free Covid-19 vaccine below</<h3>
  <h2> Information </h2>
  <ul>
    <li> If you do not know your Eircode find it <a class="info" href="https://finder.eircode.ie/#/"> here</a> </li>
    <li> Your PPS Number can be found on payslips, public service cards, medical card or GP visit cardor letters from the Revenue Commissioners or the Department of Social Protection </li>
    <li> If you are unable to find your PPS number you can contact the department of Social Protection at (01) 704 3000 </li>
    <li> You are not able to choose which vaccine you will receive unless you have obtained permission from your GP due to a medical condition </li>
    <li> If you are younger then 44 you cannot to register for the vaccine at this stage but you can refer to the <a href="page3.html" class="info">Vaccine Roll-out Schedule</a> to find out when you will be able to register </li>
  </ul>
